# Printonet Multi-Tenant Platform

Bootstrap for a centralized WordPress Multisite + WooCommerce tenant engine on a VPS.

## What this includes

- VPS bootstrap script for Ubuntu (Nginx, PHP-FPM, MariaDB, Redis, WP-CLI)
- WordPress Multisite install script (subdomain mode)
- Shared MU plugin scaffold (`printonet-core`) with tenant provisioning API
- Shared storefront theme scaffold (`printonet-storefront`)
- Environment template for secure configuration

## Directory layout

- `scripts/` - server and app bootstrap scripts
- `config/` - Nginx/PHP snippets
- `wp-content/mu-plugins/printonet-core/` - shared business logic (all tenants)
- `wp-content/themes/printonet-storefront/` - shared storefront theme
- `docs/` - API contracts and implementation notes

## Quick start

1. Copy env template and fill values:
   - `cp .env.example .env`
2. Run base bootstrap:
   - `sudo bash scripts/bootstrap_vps.sh .env`
3. Install WordPress Multisite:
   - `sudo bash scripts/install_wp_multisite.sh .env`

## Next steps

- Point wildcard DNS: `*.your-platform-domain.com` to the VPS IP
- Add wildcard TLS certificate
- Connect your existing "new store" plugin from main Printonet to:
  - `POST /wp-json/printonet/v1/provision-store`
